  "response": "London is generally considered a safe city for solo travelers, but like any major metropolitan area, it's important to take standard precautions:\n\n1. Safety tips:\n- Be aware of your surroundings\n- Keep valuables secure and out of sight\n- Use well-lit and populated routes, especially at night\n- Stay in reputable neighborhoods\n- Use licensed taxis or official transportation\n- Keep emergency contact numbers handy\n\n2. Generally safe areas:\n- Central London\n- Tourist areas\n- Most public transportation\n- Well-populated neighborhoods like Kensington, Chelsea, Westminster\n\n3. Areas to be more cautious:\n- Late at night in less populated areas\n- Some outer suburbs\n- Areas with higher crime rates like parts of East London\n\n4. Additional precautions:\n- Use official tube and bus services\n- Keep a charged phone\n- Trust your instincts\n- Consider travel insurance\n\n5. Positive factors:\n- Large police presence\n- Good public transportation\n- High tourist infrastructure\n- Generally friendly environment\n\nWhile no city is 100% safe, London is considered relatively safe for solo travelers who remain alert and take basic precautions.",
